<|> ğğšğ¦ğ¢ğ§ğ  ğ¨ğŸ ğ•ğšğ«ğ¢ğšğ›ğ¥ğğ¬ <|>
       A set of rules for naming a Python variables.

          >> A variable name must start with a letter , underscore character.
          >> A variable cannot start with a number.
          >> A variable name can only contain alpha-numeric characters and underscore ( 0-9 , A - z and _ ).
          >> Variable name are case sensitive ( Age , age , AGE - Different three variable).

            -- Example of Variables --

